input_str: Social mobility, the ability for an individual, no matter his familial background, to move up or down the social ladder, is part of the American conscience. The idea that anyone can be the president, a doctor, a businessman, or an inventor is pervasive in our culture. In fact, those on the lower end of the social pyramid are often blamed for lacking effort (from conservatives) or deemed as victims of discrimination, whether blatant or hidden (from liberals).
